{"kind":"cas-record-v1","metadata":{"entries":[{"origin_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/cli","target_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/subscriptions/openaisub","identifier":"Login","question":"When Login is called with LoginOptions.Options.Path empty, does it save credentials to the default ~/.codalotl/openai_auth.json path?","answer":"Yes.\n\nWhen `Login(ctx, LoginOptions{Options: Options{Path: \"\"}})` is called, it uses the default auth path:\n\n- `Login` computes `path := authPath(opts.Options)`.\n- `authPath` returns `DefaultPath()` when `Options.Path` is empty.\n- `DefaultPath()` returns `cascade.ExpandPath(\"~/.codalotl/openai_auth.json\")`.\n- `cascade.ExpandPath` is documented to expand leading `~` to the user’s home directory.\n- After the device login/token exchange succeeds and credentials are valid, `Login` calls `saveAuth(path, auth)`.\n\nSo on a successful login with an empty `Path`, credentials are saved to the expanded default path equivalent to `~/.codalotl/openai_auth.json`.\n\nLimit: it only saves after the login flow completes successfully and returns usable credentials."},{"origin_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/cli","target_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/subscriptions/openaisub","identifier":"LogoutWithOptions","question":"When LogoutWithOptions or CheckStatusWithOptions are called with Options.Path empty, do they operate on the same default ~/.codalotl/openai_auth.json path?","answer":"Yes.\n\nDocumented behavior:\n- `SPEC.md` says auth is stored in `~/.codalotl/openai_auth.json` by default.\n- `DefaultPath()` is documented as returning the default OpenAI subscription auth file path.\n\nImplementation facts:\n- `LogoutWithOptions(opts)` calls `os.Remove(authPath(opts))`.\n- `CheckStatusWithOptions(ctx, opts)` calls `loadAuth(opts)`, and `loadAuth` reads from `authPath(opts)`.\n- `authPath(opts)` does:\n\n```go\nif opts.Path != \"\" {\n    return cascade.ExpandPath(opts.Path)\n}\nreturn DefaultPath()\n```\n\n- `DefaultPath()` returns:\n\n```go\ncascade.ExpandPath(\"~/.codalotl/openai_auth.json\")\n```\n\nSo with `Options.Path == \"\"`, both `LogoutWithOptions` and `CheckStatusWithOptions` use the same default path: expanded `~/.codalotl/openai_auth.json`.\n\nAlso, `cascade.ExpandPath` is documented to expand leading `~` to the user home directory, so this is intended to resolve to the user’s home-based auth file path."}]},"additional_info":{"unix_timestamp":1779757076,"paths":["internal/subscriptions/openaisub/SPEC.md","internal/subscriptions/openaisub/openaisub.go","internal/subscriptions/openaisub/openaisub_test.go"],"git_clean":false,"git_commit":"5030614f157001b49caf4c6f1e334a063443319e","git_merge_base":"92686e8927e891ac21e42a7b11adc0931a0d703f"}}